<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIGAR SMOKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My husband and I have had season tickets to the USC home games for about 25 
years and were in attendance at the USC-Arizona game Oct. 20 in the Coliseum. 
</P>
<P>
During half-time we were astounded to see two very pleasant, well-behaved men 
who sit near us being handled roughly, grasped by their shirt collars and 
hustled out of Tunnel 19 by four policemen, two to each man. We didn't know 
what their offense was, but later learned they were indeed guilty -- of smoking 
cigars! 
</P>
<P>
When murder, rape and robbery abound in the area, four policemen are busy 
stamping out cigar smoking! Has the world gone mad or is it only in Los 
Angeles? 
</P>
<P>
ALICE SHEQUEN, La Crescenta 
</P>
</TEXT>
