<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 SLAIN, 2 HURT IN GANG FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bloody street brawl between rival gangs in Van Nuys this weekend left one 
youth dead and two others injured, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Armed with guns, knives and baseball bats, as many as eight members of two 
rival gangs clashed in a melee that erupted in the 13200 block of Vanowen 
Street about 8:20 p.m., on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
When police arrived they found Jesus G. Gilberto, 17, of North Hollywood 
mortally wounded by gunshots. 
</P>
<P>
The teen-ager died two hours later at Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Two other victims of the same brawl arrived at another hospital for treatment a 
short time later. A 21-year-old North Hollywood man was in critical but stable 
condition with a stab wound, while an 18-year-old, also from North Hollywood, 
was treated for injuries caused by a baseball bat, police said. The 18-year-old 
was treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
Neither of the men was identified, and police did not say if the two men or the 
dead youth were gang members. The two men were not arrested. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they were looking for others involved and had not determined what 
sparked the confrontation. 
</P>
<P>
Residents living in apartment buildings in the neighborhood said they heard 
shouting in the street, followed by a series of gunshots in quick succession. 
After the shots, they said, as many as seven people fled from Vanowen and Atoll 
Avenue, leaving the dead youth behind in the street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
