<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
CANDIDATES' FORUM SCHEDULED TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOEL BRAND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oxnard City Council and mayoral candidates will get a chance to present their 
views to both English-speaking and Spanish-speaking voters Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
A three-hour forum, sponsored by the League of Women Voters and a variety of 
local civic groups, will give the public a chance to meet the 12 council 
candidates and six mayoral candidates. 
</P>
<P>
At stake are two council seats and the mayorship. 
</P>
<P>
Because Oxnard is more than 50% Hispanic, the event's sponsors believed that it 
would be appropriate to offer on-the-spot Spanish translation, as well as 
Spanish and English telecasts of the event, said Gloria Postel, a League of 
Women Voters member and coordinator of the forum. 
</P>
<P>
Questions for the forum will be formulated by both the Oxnard Community College 
students and the audience. The forum will be held in the community college's 
Room LA 6 from 7 to 10 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
A videotape of the forum has been scheduled, twice in English and twice in 
Spanish, for Oxnard cable subscribers later in the week on Channel 19. JOEL 
BRAND 
</P>
</TEXT>
