<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / A GLANCE AT THIS WEEK IN THE NFL; 
</P>
<P>
SMALL VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Detroit's 27-10 victory over New Orleans was the Saints' third loss to a 
run-and-shoot offense in four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
The Saints, ranked eighth in the NFC in team defense, lost to Houston, 23-10, 
last week and to Atlanta, 28-27, three weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
Reaching for a positive note, the Saints can offer only defensive end Jim 
Wilks, who registered their first sack of a run-and-shoot quarterback this 
season when he got to Rodney Peete in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Peete, however, was only momentarily grounded. The former USC quarterback got 
up and completed 16 of 24 passes for 246 yards, including a five-yard touchdown 
pass to Robert Clark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
