<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Marla Cone and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MYSTERY OF THE DEEP: The extremely rare megamouth shark captured off Dana Point 
last week is only the latest in a series of local marine oddities. . . . Over 
the past two years, usually rare sea turtles, sea otters, huge Risso's 
dolphins, blue whale, sperm whale, minke whale, king salmon and giant squid 
have been sighted. On the other hand, normally plentiful sharks and white 
croakers are scarce. . . . What's going on? "I don't completely understand it," 
says marine biologist Dennis Kelly of Orange Coast College, who has monitored 
the county's sea life for 22 years. "Everyone wants answers, but we don't have 
them." Marla Cone and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
