<P>
POST PARTUM: Robert Lavenberg, above, the first scientist to examine the Dana 
Point megamouth shark, is nonetheless down in the dumps. 
</P>
<P>
Professional disappointment? No, melancholy after releasing the fish. . . . 
"There is a bonding that occurs, and it's like a divorce, an end to a 
relationship," he says. "But at least he's OK. And we learned a hell of a lot 
about a very rare shark. Now the real work begins." Marla Cone and Steve Emmons 
</P>
