<P>
PACIFIC FALLS DESPITE KOPP'S RECORD NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Garrett Gabriel passed for three touchdowns as Hawaii beat the University of 
the Pacific, 35-24, Saturday night despite a record-setting performance by 
Tiger quarterback Troy Kopp. 
</P>
<P>
Kopp, a graduate of Mission Viejo High School, completed 42 of 73 passes for 
