<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEEDS OF PEOPLE ALREADY HERE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Instead of just listening to the proponents' tune that the Measure A sales tax 
is a necessity, think about some alternatives. Think about needs that are not 
being met in our neighborhoods and cities. 
</P>
<P>
Think about the need for adequate child care in thousands of families every 
day. Think about the need for adequate advance training to help high school 
graduates enter the work force. Think about preservation of open space so that 
Ventura County doesn't become wall-to-wall houses as is typical of the San 
Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Before giving a half-billion dollars to pay for road improvements that will 
open new land for development and help make certain landowners rich, think 
instead about the needs of our families and neighbors. Then ask: Couldn't the 
same money be better spent on meeting the health, education and environmental 
quality needs of people who are already here? 
</P>
<P>
ANDY PROKOPOW 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 
</P>
