<TEXT>
<P>
Bartender Keith Thomlinson got the biggest tip of his life last week -- a 
lottery ticket worth $25,000. 
</P>
<P>
Lottery officials said today that Thomlinson, 42, a bartender at the Green 
House Inn and Restaurant, scratched off a Rhode Island lottery Baseball game 
ticket while cleaning the bar Friday and discovered he had won $25,000. 
</P>
<P>
The ticket was a gift Thursday night from Newport resident Russell Clark, who 
frequents bars and often leaves lottery tickets as tips, according to Ray 
Grimes, deputy director of the Rhode Island lottery. 
