<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WOOSNAM'S $1 MILLION TOPS LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VIRGINIA WATER, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ian Woosnam, who went over the $1-million mark for a season for the first time 
and set a career-earnings record, finished first on the PGA European Tour 
money-winning list. 
</P>
<P>
Woosnam tied Sandy Lyle for 21st place in the season-ending Volvo Masters at 
Stogrande, Spain, on Sunday, earning him $10,776. He clinched the earnings 
championship when his closest pursuer, Zimbabwe's Mark McNulty, finished in a 
four-way tie for fourth and won $35,207. 
</P>
<P>
Woosnam, from Wales, finished the season with $1,125,365, compared with 
$994,780 for McNulty. Jose Maria Olazabal of Spain was third, with $852,141. 
</P>
<P>
Woosnam's career earnings on the European tour climbed to a record $3.92 
million. 
</P>
<P>
The top American was Rick Hartmann, who finished 39th with $183,677. 
</P>
</TEXT>
