<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
FILM FEATURES NOVELIST'S HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cobblestones will be put down today in front of novelist Anne Rice's house, 
where a movie company is filming part of a movie based on Kate Chopin's novel 
"The Awakening," starring Kelly McGillis. 
</P>
<P>
The novel, set in the 1880s, is about a woman who rejects Victorian moral and 
sexual standards, with tragic consequences. Along with playing its main 
character, artist Edna Pontellier, McGillis also is the executive producer. 
</P>
<P>
Rice's house turned out to be unexpectedly perfect for the Pontellier mansion 
because her husband, Stan, paints and has a studio on the third floor. 
</P>
<P>
"Our search for a third-floor atelier -- I guess that's French for studio? -- 
ended when we found that Stan already had one," location manager Mike Neale 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
